EC2
+ you own the machine
+ lots of tutorials on the web (mongodb, node, ...)
- need to choose right geographic location
- complicated interface

Cloud Foundry
+ support node.js (example: http://docs.cloudfoundry.com/frameworks/nodejs/nodejs.html)
+ support mongo-node (http://docs.cloudfoundry.com/services/mongodb/nodejs-mongodb.html)
+ test locally then push
- command line console called 'vmc'  
- beta version
- - no pricing available

Heroku
- weird teminology
- costly
+ node.js (https://devcenter.heroku.com/categories/nodejs)
+ mongohq

Cloudbees
- java only
- Complicated. I find the doc not easy to find (Simon)
+ jenkins
+ mongohq (see the price at http://www.cloudbees.com/platform-service-mongohq.cb)
- I did not like. It was very slow for me. Although a long time ago in 2012 (Simon)